Ad Text:
We are currently recruiting for a Queensland Government client to recruit an experienced Portfolio Analyst to join a high‑performing Portfolio Management Office supporting a large‑scale infrastructure and capital works portfolio.

This is an excellent opportunity for a skilled analyst to work in a complex, highly visible environment, contributing to executive‑level reporting and governance decision‑making across a diverse program of work.

The opportunity

In this role, you will support the delivery of portfolio performance reporting and insights, working closely with PMO, finance and delivery teams. You will play a key role in consolidating and analysing portfolio data to ensure senior stakeholders have clear, accurate and timely information to support investment, risk and performance decisions.

Key responsibilities

Deliver monthly and quarterly portfolio performance reports, dashboards, and visualisations.
Coordinate, validate and consolidate portfolio data across multiple programs and business areas.
Analyse portfolio performance to identify trends, risks and improvement opportunities.
Support the development of executive briefings, governance papers and performance summaries.
Maintain and enhance reporting tools, templates and frameworks using Power BI, Excel, and related platforms.
Engage with stakeholders to ensure reporting aligns with portfolio objectives and governance requirements.

About you

You will be an experienced analyst with a background in portfolio, program or performance reporting within a government or large, complex organisation. You are detail-focused, comfortable working with data, and confident in producing reporting for senior audiences.

You will bring:

Demonstrated experience in portfolio or performance reporting.
Strong analytical and problem-solving skills.
Experience developing executive-level reports and dashboards.
Proficiency in Power BI, Excel and reporting tools.
Strong written and verbal communication skills

Experience within infrastructure, capital works or public sector environments will be highly regarded.

What's on offer

Hour Rate of $99.93 per hour inc. super
Brisbane location, with hybrid working arrangements available.
Opportunity to work within a large‑scale Queensland Government infrastructure portfolio.
Secure contract / permanent opportunity (depending on appointment) within a collaborative PMO environment.
Full support and guidance from a specialist recruitment partner throughout the process.

To apply, please click Apply Now.
For a confidential discussion, contact Laura Syms at Laura.Syms@empiregroup

At Empire Group, we value diversity and are committed to equitable recruitment. We encourage Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples, people from culturally diverse backgrounds, people with disability, and other underrepresented groups to apply. Our focus is on creating fair, accessible, and culturally safe recruitment processes that genuinely reflect and respect the communities we serve.

Company description:



Insignia Financial Limited is an Australian financial services company which offers a range of products and services including financial advice, superannuation, investment management and trustee services



Job description:


Be a part of a major transformation in investment administration with real impact across systems and platforms.
Work on high-profile projects in a collaborative, agile, and business-led environment.
Shape the future of superannuation technology while growing your leadership and domain expertise.

The opportunity to join our team


Are you ready to lead one of the most significant investment administration transformations in Australia's superannuation sector?



At Insignia Financial, we're embarking on a multi-year journey to simplify and modernise our investment systems — and we're looking for a Senior Business Analyst to help us make it happen. This is your chance to work on high-impact initiatives that will define the future of our proprietary platforms and improve outcomes for millions of Australians.



You'll be joining a passionate, collaborative team leading a major transformation of our investment administration systems, focused on consolidating platforms, enhancing our proprietary UNISON system, and designing a new, future-ready pricing model.



As a Senior Business Analyst, you'll play a key role in shaping and delivering this transformation. You'll work closely with business stakeholders, delivery leads, and technology teams to:

Lead business and system analysis across discovery, development, testing, and delivery phases.
Translate complex business needs into clear, actionable user stories and acceptance criteria.
Support UAT and functionality testing, ensuring solutions meet business expectations.
Partner with product owners to define value, prioritise requirements, and articulate the product vision.
Coach and support other analysts, lifting capability across the team.
Navigate ambiguity and drive clarity in a fast-paced, evolving environment.


You'll be working on projects that include:

Consolidating four registry systems into one.
Consolidating from 3 unit pricing systems to 1.
Defining a new, flexible pricing model - the biggest uplift in UNISON in 20 years.
Supporting the migration of off-platform funds into UNISON.
Contributing to cost optimisation and scale initiatives aligned to our MasterTrust roadmap.

What You Bring to This Role


To thrive in this role, you'll need to bring a strong mix of domain expertise, analytical leadership, and delivery experience. Specifically, we're looking for:

Deep experience in Business Analysis within a software development team, ideally within superannuation or investment administration.
Firm understanding of:
Fund administration & accounting
Unit pricing and distributions
Custody services and general ledger accounting
Investment platforms like pControl, HiPortfolio, and UNISON (preferred, not essential)
Experience in technology transformation programs, especially platform migrations.
Strong stakeholder engagement and communication skills.
Agile delivery experience and comfort working with ambiguity.
Certifications like CBAP, AAC, or Scrum Master are a plus.

Find the better way

What gets us excited about working here? Helping people feel good about their money as one of Australia's leading financial wellbeing organisations. From those starting out to those retiring. As your team, we'll show up for you and together we will create financial wellbeing for every Australian. Because we know people who are confident about their financial future live better lives.

If this sounds like your kind of career, you sound like our kind of person. With us, you'll do work that builds your technical know-how and challenges our entire industry to move forward. Along the way, you'll be free to explore new ideas and technology, solve problems in a team, and independently to get great things done. Around here, we like to call it "putting our fingerprints on the future".

People-inspired tech

Deep expertise combined with creativity can take on the trickiest of problems. Join our team of brilliant minds and mentors as we explore our way to innovation and apply technology in more human ways than ever.

__

To Apply

Read more here about why you should join our team.

Applicants will be required to provide evidence of their eligibility to work in Australia, and at a minimum be required to undertake police and basic credit checks as a condition of employment.

Please note that applications from agencies will not be considered at this time.

We acknowledge and celebrate the richness that individual differences bring to our team. If you need assistance or an adjustment during the application process, please reach out and let us know.

Company: Talent – Specialists in tech, transformation & beyond
Ad Text:
Senior Machine Learning Engineer
Initial 6-Month Contract
Surry Hills, Sydney - Hybrid Work Model

About the Role
The Data and Insights Branch is seeking an experienced Senior Machine Learning Engineer to lead the design, development, and deployment of advanced AI and machine learning solutions that support our agency's strategic goals. This pivotal role will drive data-driven decision-making and deliver innovative, ethical AI capabilities within a secure, compliant environment.

As an EL1 ML Engineer, you will provide technical leadership, collaborate with DVA data professionals, and ensure the implementation of robust, scalable, and responsible machine learning solutions across the organisation. Initially, you will focus on understanding and leveraging the GovAI platform and the existing AWS DVA/Services Australia environment, with a key role in supporting DVA's Cloud Roadmap.

Eligibility Criteria

Australian Citizen
Ability to obtain and maintain a minimum Baseline security clearance

Key Responsibilities

Design and develop machine learning models and algorithms for complex datasets
Build and maintain end-to-end ML pipelines for training, testing, and deployment
Optimize models for performance, scalability, and accuracy in production settings
Collaborate with data scientists, engineers, and stakeholders to translate requirements into technical solutions
Ensure compliance with Australian Government security frameworks (ISM, PSPF) and uphold ethical AI principles
Implement monitoring and maintenance processes, including data drift detection and model lifecycle management
Provide technical guidance, mentorship, and capability development within the team
Stay informed of emerging ML technologies and industry best practices

Essential Skills & Experience

Proven experience in machine learning engineering within complex environments
Proficiency in Python and ML frameworks such as TensorFlow, PyTorch, Scikit-learn
Strong background in data engineering, feature engineering, and model optimization
Experience with ML Ops tools and practices (Kubeflow, MLflow, Airflow)
Hands-on experience with cloud platforms (AWS, Azure, GCP) and containerization (Docker, Kubernetes)
Excellent problem-solving skills, with the ability to manage multiple priorities
Strong communication skills and ability to engage stakeholders effectively

Join Us
If you're passionate about leveraging AI to make a meaningful impact and meet the above criteria, we want to hear from you!

How to Apply:
Please submit your CV and cover letter in Word format by clicking the "APPLY NOW" button below or email your application to anna.au@talentinternational.com.

8+ years of relevant professional experience working as a data scientist.

A passion for using AI and data for business transformation and a thirst to continually learn and keep pace with the latest innovations and applications. 

Experience in statistical methods and modelling techniques (e.g., Random Forests, Clustering, Linear Regression) and expertise in key areas such as customer intelligence (segmentation, behavior analysis, personalization, recommender systems, forecasting). 

Experience using and integrating generative AI models and platforms, agentic solutions, and context engineering techniques. 

Experience with programming languages (Python, R, SQL) and AI/ML platforms (e.g. Databricks, and cloud platforms (e.g. Azure Synapse, AWS SageMaker, Google Cloud Vertex AI). 

Experience with data science, data visualization, and data analysis tools (e.g., scikit-learn, pandas and NumPy, Apache Spark, matplotlib, ggplot2). 

Experience working with large volume data sets and multiple data formats and interfaces (SQL, JSON, REST, Parquet, streaming, geospatial, unstructured).

Technical knowledge of reporting and data visualization tools (Tableau & Power BI), graphing and chart libraries (e.g., matplotlib, plotly). 

Experience working in a client-facing (ideally) consulting role, having great written and verbal communication skills, and the ability to work closely with stakeholders, or having been part of a project team.

Flexibility and the willingness to travel are required for this role, as you might need to spend time on-site with our clients.

Experience in agile methodologies and relevant tools (Confluence, Jira, git).

Experience working in cross-cultural and cross-disciplinary teams. 

Desired Qualifications 

Understanding of data (management) platforms (CDP, CRM, DMP, Big Data Lakes, Cloud) and tools (ETL, Processing, marketing automation, etc.).

Experience in production environments for Machine Learning products, knowledge of the tools that are needed for model deployment and lifecycle management in ML engineering (Docker, Kubernetes).

Solid knowledge of software engineering principles & deployment methods (preferably in cloud environments).  Experience in data-driven marketing, campaign development, measurement, and optimization, Martech, CDP, etc.

Industry experience in the Finance, Automotive, Logistics, Energy, or public sector.

Your new opportunity 
Take on a meaningful leadership role in shaping Queensland's social policy under the Social Policy and Analytics branch of Queensland Treasury. As the Principal Treasury Analyst, you will provide expert advice and oversight of critical social policy frameworks and initiatives, supporting government-wide priorities and championing evidence-based decision-making for the benefit of Queensland communities.  

Set in a dynamic, fast-paced environment, this role offers the opportunity to create impactful solutions that address complex policy challenges. Join us and bring your expertise to the forefront of Queensland's strategic policy agenda.

In this role, you will: 
•    Lead and coordinate the delivery of a complex program of social policy analysis and initiatives. 
•    Develop and deliver strategic, practical, and solutions-focused advice on social policy frameworks and programs to internal and external stakeholders, ensuring alignment with the government's priorities. 
•    Exercise sound judgment, provide authoritative advice, and influence stakeholders to balance client needs and team goals. 
•    Offer leadership and direction to team members executing multi-dimensional projects, while delivering guidance and support to senior executives and clients. 
•    Build and maintain strong relationships with key stakeholders to address challenging and complex policy issues. 
•    Represent Queensland Treasury in high-level consultations, negotiations, and forums—ensuring consistent and professional advocacy of policy priorities.

What experience you will bring: 
•    Demonstrated experience in program and project management or in advancing proactive, evidence-based policy agendas across multi-disciplinary teams. 
•    A strong ability to prepare and deliver strategic and actionable policy advice. 
•    A desire and proven ability to inspire meaningful change and drive policy outcomes. 
•    Highly effective communication skills, both written and verbal, with the ability to tailor messaging to diverse stakeholders and audiences. 
•    Strong interpersonal and relationship management skills, fostering collaboration and information sharing among stakeholders.

Whilst there are no mandatory qualifications needed for this role, relevant qualifications will be highly regarded.  

How to apply 
To submit your application, click on the Apply link to provide: 
•    Your resume detailing relevant experience 
•    A cover letter of no more than two pages outlining why you are interested in this position and how your knowledge, skills and experience makes you a strong candidate for the role.  

Queensland Treasury is committed to building an inclusive and diverse workforce that reflects the community we serve and treating all applicants equitably. This starts with recruitment, including making reasonable adjustments to support applicants at all stages of the process.  

We welcome applicants to share with the hiring manager any health condition, disability, and/or cultural or linguistic background, so that we may make any necessary adjustments to enable you to equitably participate in the recruitment process.



Applications to remain current for 12 months
